data.title: Best Desserts Ever!
data.text:
Everything I've tried has been delicious. 
But this is the BEST german chocolate cake I have ever had.

data.title: Best Sugar Coma EVA~
data.text: We used them for our wedding and they were such a hit the cake sat there like it had no friends. I love this place and if my waistline could afford it we would be there at least every weekend for a sweet treat.

data.title: Sweet Red Peach - Delicious
data.text: If you enjoy great pastries this is the place. My favorite is Red Velvet my wife's is Lemon but we like everything. We've tried many of their treats and give them as gifts to others. Everything is freshly made with quality ingredients. New location, call 310 671 2253 for address and store hours - info@sweetredpeach.com - log onto their website to see what they offer.  Sign-up for discounts, too.  We love it and believe you will too!

data.title: Cocoanut Pineapple Cake to die for!
data.text: Hidden gem in Inglewood. The cakes and cupcakes are very moist and delicious. They also make scrumptious cookies. My favorite is the coconut pineapple cake, which also comes in a cupcake. They don't make it everyday only on Saturdays, but if you are not there by noon, you'll miss out. Their cake slices are large. Usually enough for 2 servings.

data.title: Every flavor imaginable
data.text:
We found Sweet Red Peach through Bludso's bbq in  mpton. They gave me a slice of 7up cake. So, next visit to the South Bay we drove up to Inglewood to get MORE CAKE!

Tucked into a strip mall across from old Hollywood Park. The cupcakes are divine. $1.75 for mini cupcakes,  3.75 for regular. 

Really helpful , patient girls at the counter. Lots and lots to choose from. 

Highly recommend
